Package dk.jakobhandersen.multiregionexporterforcubase

Class CubaseTrackXMLSaxParseHandler

java.lang.Object
org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
dk.jakobhandersen.multiregionexporterforcubase.CubaseTrackXMLSaxParseHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler
public class CubaseTrackXMLSaxParseHandler
extends org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
Extension of DefaultHandler to be used with SAXParser. Parses the Cubase track XML file and creates AudioBite objects. Note: I have no previous experience in working with SAX parsing, so this class might not be very elegant. A future task will be to either review and refine this parser or to write another non-SAX parser. Also, there is currently quite a lot of duplicate code for the different event types that could be encapsulated. And furthermore an idea could be to change from first checking the qName of the element into first checking the relevant attribute. Inspiration: http://www.journaldev.com/1198/java-sax-parser-example-tutorial-to-parse-xml-to-list-of-objects Inspiration: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/jaxp/sax/parsing.html
Author:
Jakob Hougaard Andersen

    • currentPAudioClipID

      private java.lang.String currentPAudioClipID
      The ID of the PAudioClip element we are currently parsing. Is only relevant if we are in fact currently parsing a PAudioClip element. Is used for handling naming fall-back to audio clip name. Note that only the first occurrence of a given audio clip obj node (@class = PAudioClip) will have other info than its ID - e.g. its name.

    • audioClipIdNameMap

      private java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> audioClipIdNameMap
      Maps from audio clip ID to name. Note that only the first occurrence of a given audio clip obj node (@class = PAudioClip) will have other info than its ID - e.g. its name. The next ones (no class attribute) will just have the ID.

    • numRenamedAudioBites
